  "title": "Proposal: Align menu and connectMenu behaviour with RIS Menu",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nA feature/bug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nWhen using a **menu** with **React InstantSearch**, we get this behaviour:\r\n\r\n![2018-01-25 14 41 37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/123822/35391093-ebcb53c2-01dd-11e8-80f2-7dd70862bb29.gif)\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n- Load the [HierarchicalMenu story](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/storybook/?selectedKind=HierarchicalMenu&selectedStory=default&full=0&addons=1&stories=1&panelRight=1&addonPanel=storybooks%2Fstorybook-addon-knobs)\r\n- Click on Lighting\r\n- Type/search \"boholmen\"\r\n\r\n**But** when using a **menu** with **InstantSearch.js**, we get this behaviour:\r\n\r\n![2018-01-25 14 56 26](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/123822/35391785-ff9b4e1e-01df-11e8-969c-39fcb7623c26.gif)\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n- Load the [example](https://codesandbox.io/s/8zpoxz7jw0)\r\n- Click on Lighting\r\n- Type/search \"boholmen\"\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nIt should still show other matching categories as a way to allow the user to have more context.\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is the proposed solution?**\r\n\r\nSwitch from hierarchical facet to disjunctive facet in the menu implementation.",
